LanguageTool (rules, confusion sets, morphology)  —  LGPL-2.1
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The L2 rule corpus and L3 confusion sets are derived from LanguageTool
(https://github.com/languagetool-org/languagetool), LGPL-2.1. Build artifacts
derived from this data (resources/en.rkyv, resources/confusion.rkyv) are LGPL-2.1
and are not committed; they are produced on demand.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
L4 edit-tagger model  —  NON-COMMERCIAL
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The optional L4 layer derives its model from:

  gotutiyan/gector-roberta-base-5k
  https://huggingface.co/gotutiyan/gector-roberta-base-5k
  Trained weights are licensed for NON-COMMERCIAL use only.

  An unofficial PyTorch implementation of GECToR (Omelianchuk et al., 2020,
  "GECToR — Grammatical Error Correction: Tag, Not Rewrite").

The exported/quantized artifact (resources/l4/*) is a derivative of those weights
and is non-commercial. Any distribution bundling it is non-commercial (PolyForm
Noncommercial 1.0.0). The artifact is not committed; it is produced by pipeline/.

The verb-form transform dictionary (resources/l4/verb-form-vocab.txt) is from
Grammarly's GECToR (https://github.com/grammarly/gector).

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Norvig n-grams (L3 statistical confusion)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
L3 uses Peter Norvig's Google-corpus n-gram subsets (https://norvig.com/ngrams/),
fetched on demand, pruned to LanguageTool's confusion words.
